19 SECTION 2. Section 16-21.1-1 of the General Laws in Chapter 16-21.1 entitled
20 "Transportation of School Pupils Beyond City and Town Limits [See Title 16 Chapter 97 — The
21 Rhode Island Board of Education Act]" is hereby amended to read as follows:
22 16-21.1-1. General purposes.
23 This chapter shall be construed and applied to:
24 (1) Create a state plan for the busing of pupils beyond city or town limits, in recognition of
25 the legislative policy to encourage the establishment of and continuance of consolidated and
26 regional schools;
27 (2) Provide a unified statewide busing service;
28 (3) Afford to pupils who attend public schools the opportunity at the election of the school
29 committee of the city or town in which the pupils reside to attend a public school, either full time
30 or part time, outside of the city or town which provides a program or curriculum not available
31 within the city or town in which the pupil resides, as authorized by § 16-3.1-1 et seq.;
32 (4) Afford to children with disabilities equal educational opportunity;
33 (5) Afford bus transportation to pupils who attend nonpublic nonprofit schools which are
34 consolidated, regionalized, or otherwise established to serve residents of a specific area within the
